==Etymology==
:Latin: ''vernaculus'', meaning ''native'' or ''indigenous''. The original meaning was ''belonging to homeborn slaves''.

===Noun===
#everyday speech, as opposed to [[literary]] or [[liturgical]] [[language]].
#language unique to a particular group of people; [[jargon]].

